        * base/i386/hal/hal.immed: reworked all the enabling/disabling
	  interrupt controllers functions to hopefully work from 2.4.36
	  to 2.6.38; added a check for possible NULL pointers also.

2012-01-09 Pierangelo Masarati <masarati@aero.polimi.it>

	* RTAI 3.9-test1

2012-01-09 Pierangelo Masarati <masarati@aero.polimi.it>

	* configure configure.in: fix build out of source dir

2012-01-07 Paolo Mantegazza <mantegazza@aero.polimi.it>

        * base/x86_64/hal/hal.immed and base/i386/hal/hal.immed: use
	  IPIPE_HEAD_PRIORITY for the RTAI domain.

2012-01-04 Pierangelo Masarati <masarati@aero.polimi.it>

	* configure.in, rtai_config.h: add support for Linux COMEDI.
        * configure.in, rtai_config.h: add support for setting COMEDI locks
          by default.
	* configure, rtai_config.h, [*/]GNUmakefile.in: regenerate with
	  different autotools (automake 1.11.1, libtoolize 2.2.6b,
	  autoconf 2.67).

2012-01-03 Paolo Mantegazza <mantegazza@aero.polimi.it>

        * base/x86_64/hal/hal.immed: updated to work with Linux up to
	  2.6.38.
        * base/x86_64/hal/rtai_fpu.h: add FPU_ENV compatibility for
          Linux > 2.6.34.
        * base/x86_64/hal/rtai_hal.h: upgraded macros definition to support
	  Linux > 2.6.34.

2012-01-02 Paolo Mantegazza <mantegazza@aero.polimi.it>

        * addons/comedi/README: add explanations about using native LINUX
	  COMEDI and remote/distributed COMEDI.
        * addons/comedi/patchlinuxcomedi: shell script for patching native
	  Linux COMEDI.
        * addons/comedi/rtai_comedi.h: rework and reorder previous layout
          setup make it possible to use COMEDI as found in Linux kernels;
	  add netrpc based support for remote/distributed COMEDI usage.
        * addons/comedi/kcomedi-module.c: set the interface to native Linux
	  COMEDI within this module, to avoid touching RTAI hal module and
	  to be usable on any arch; set safe pointers at module cleanup to
	  avoid oopses in between rtai_comedi module removal and the full
	  closure of an application; add specific functions to support
          remote/distributed COMEDI commands and instructions.
	* base/arch/i386/Kconfig: make default use of COMEDI lock configurable.

2012-01-01 Paolo Mantegazza <mantegazza@aero.polimi.it>

        * base/ipc/msg/msg.c: revised sendx, previous implementation could
	  overwrite previous sends, made rt_sendx_if safer for in interrupt
	  handlers usage, strengthened correctness check of task args and
	  copying into pointed variables, receivex-es should have more
	  appropriate returns now.

2011-12-31 Roberto Bucher <roberto.bucher@supsi.ch>

	* rtai-lab/scicoslab/macros/RTAI/RTAICodeGen_.sci: if state are not
	  present, code for state update is not generated.
	* rtai-lab/scicoslab/macros/RTAI/RTAICodeGen_.sci: scicosim is not
	  started by creating code, avoiding problems with blocks used for
	  HIL (thanks to Klaus Weichinger).
	
2011-12-31 Paolo Mantegazza <mantegazza@aero.polimi.it>

	* base/sched/sched.c and sys.c: if PF_EVNOTIFY is defined use the
	  related Linux patch service, instead of or-ring the related flag
	  directly.
	* addons/rtdm/device.c: avoid DECLARE_MUTEX, use the related struct
	  declaration and initialize it explicitly at module init.
	* base/arch/i386/hal/hal.immed: upgraded to work up to Linux 2.6.38.8.

2011-12-29 Paolo Mantegazza <mantegazza@aero.polimi.it>

	* base/arch/i386/hal/hal.c: put diag for APIC timers sync under ifdef.
	* base/include/asm-i386/rtai_fpu.h: upgrade to support 2.6.35.
	* base/include/asm-i386/rtai_hal.h: upgrade to support 2.6.35.
	* addons/drivers/serial/rtai_serial.h: make all declared prototypes
	  compilable in a lib.
	* rtai-py/rtai_ser.py: add RTAI serial support for python.
	* base/include/rtai_wrappers.h: define init_MUTEX_LOCKED if not
	  defined in Linux.
	* base/ipc/fifos/fifos.c: define iopl according to
	  HAVE_UNLOCKED_IOCTL.
	* base/ipc/shm/shm.c: define iopl according to
	  HAVE_UNLOCKED_IOCTL.
	* base/include/rtai_schedcore.h: resume a timed out, suspended task,
	  unconditionally, zeroing suspdepth if it is > 0: this choice allows
	  a uniform resumption mechanism both for self and externally
	  suspended tasks.
	* base/sched/api.c: resume a suspended task forced to unblock
	  unconditionally by zeroing suspdepth if it is > 0: this choice
	  allows a uniform resumption mechanism both for self and externally
	  suspended tasks; use both of the previous resulting modifications
	  for all rt_task_suspend flavours.
	* base/sched/sys.c: export rt_fun_ext for direct use in netrpc.c.
	* base/ipc/netrpc/netrpc.c: use rt_fun_ext directly, in place of
	  rt_net_rpc_fun_ext.
	* base/include/rtai_posix.h: fixed return value of pthread_cond_wait.
	* addons/rtdm/* and addons/drivers/16559A/*: upgraded to more recent
	  rtdm changes.
	* base/ipc/sem/sem.c: a higher prio task can grab a resem that is
	  owned by a task that has not been scheduled yet, "ubi maior minor
	  cessat"; mimicking Linux rt-mutexes.
	* base/sched/sched.c: use RT_TASK "running" variable to mark a truly
	  owned resource semaphores when scheduling.

2011-06-27 Roberto Bucher <roberto.bucher@supsi.ch>

	* rtai-lab/scicoslab/macros/RTAI/RTAICodeGen_.sci: Removed
	  bug on creating opar structure (thanks to Matteo Morelli)

